le Print article Cutting-edge telescopes, gravitational waves, black holes and our solar system's central star, the Sun, are just a few of the topics that will be on the table in Cape Town, South Africa, for an event that's a scientific version of the Olympic Games - though the world's leading astronomy researchers in attendance will be showcasing their brains rather than their brawn.\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23213121998297e-44, \"text\": \"Sun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\"}, {\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cape_Town\", \"score\": 0.6440612511917297, \"rank\": 0.5526473579177003, \"text\": \"Cape Town\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cape_Town\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cape_Town\"}, {\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.107131372962577e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all partners\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"gravitational waves\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"black holes\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 567}, {\"ngram\": \"our solar system's central star\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 603}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sun\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"the topics\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"a scientific version\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 737}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's leading astronomy rese