discoveries at an astonishing rate.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the telescope\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2731}, {\"ngram\": \"testing and verification phases\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2773}, {\"ngram\": \"full science operations mode\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"discoveries\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"an astonishing rate\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What makes it especially effective is that it offers astronomers the high sensitivity - the ability to detect faint, distant objects - required to study the early universe.\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"astronomers\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2931}, {\"ngram\": \"the high sensitivity\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2952}, {\"ngram\": \"the ability\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2966}, {\"ngram\": \"faint, distant objects\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"the early universe\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the assembly's symposia, titled \\\"The first chapters of our cosmic history with JWST\\\" features some of the new results in the exploration of the early universe, when the first stars and galaxies were formed.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3127, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JWST\", \"types\": [\"Q2133344\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the assembly's symposia\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3071}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"The first chapters\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"our cosmic history\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3121}, {\"ngram\": \"the new results\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3165}, {\"ngram\": \"the exploration\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3184}, {\"ngram\": \"the early universe\", \"from\": 3188, \"to\": 3206}, {\"ngram\": \"the first stars\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3228}, {\"ngram\": \"galaxies\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is fascinating for astronomers and non-astronomers alike: we are all interested in knowing whether there is another planet like ours out there, and the James Webb Space Telescope has already been used to discover many new exoplanets (planets that orbit outside our own solar system).\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3413, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Webb Space Telescope\", \"types\": [\"Q2133344\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"astronomers\", \"from\": 3280, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"non\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3299}, {\"ngram\": \"astronomers\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3311}, {\"ngram\": \"another planet\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"many new exoplanets\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3493}, {\"ngram\": \"planets\", \"from\": 3495, \"to\": 3502}, {\"ngram\": \"our own solar system\", \"from\": 3522, \"to\": 3542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Could any of these planets be habitable for humans?\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3596, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these planets\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3571}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We may have answers sooner than we expected as the telescope continues its remarkable work.\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3688, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"answers\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3616}, {\"ngram\": \"the telescope\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3657}, {\"ngram\": \"its remarkable work\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neutral hydrogenis the most abundant element in the universe and is an essential part of the makeup of galaxies in the universe.\", \"from\": 3690, \"to\": 3818, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most abundant element\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3734}, {\"ngram\": \"the universe\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3750}, {\"ngram\": \"an essential part\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3775}, {\"ngram\": \"the makeup\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3789}, {\"ngram\": \"galaxies\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3801}, {\"ngram\": \"the universe\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the spin direction of the electron in the hydrogen atom flips, radio emissions are produced.\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3916, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the electron\", \"from\": 3846, \"to\": 3858}, {\"ngram\": \"the hydrogen atom flips\", \"from\": 3862, \"to\": 3885}, {\"ngram\": \"radio emissions\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3902}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These emissions can be detected by radio telescopes and are crucial for understanding the distribution and kinematics (motion) of gases in galaxies.\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These emissions\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 3932}, {\"ngram\": \"radio telescopes\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 3968}, {\"ngram\": \"the distribution\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4019}, {\"ngram\": \"kinematics\", \"from\": 4024, \"to\": 4034}, {\"ngram\": \"motion\", \"from\": 4036, \"to\": 4042}, {\"ngram\": \"gases\", \"from\": 4047, \"to\": 4052}, {\"ngram\": \"galaxies\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MeerKAT, a precursor to the SKA, is already producing groundbreaking neutral hydrogen science because it is currently the most sensitive telescope for neutral hydrogen observations.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4095, \"end\": 4098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\", \"scor